---
import Shell from '../layouts/Shell.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.svelte';
---

<Shell title="Resources" branch="home">
  <PageHeader
    title="Resources"
    subtitle="Books, organizations, and tools to go deeper."
    branch="home"
    backHref="/"
    backLabel="Home"
  />

  <div class="px-5 pb-12">

    <!-- Books -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-stone-400 tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">Books</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-2.5">

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">The Trauma of Money</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-0.5">Chantel Chapman</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Understanding your emotional relationship with money. A practical framework for recognizing how trauma shapes financial behaviour. Essential reading.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">Indigenomics</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-0.5">Carol Anne Hilton</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">The case for Indigenous economic participation and the $100 billion Indigenous economy. Reframes the conversation from deficit to opportunity.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">Braiding Sweetgrass</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-0.5">Robin Wall Kimmerer</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Where Indigenous knowledge and science meet. Not finance-specific, but frames the seven-generation worldview that underlies everything in this app.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">21 Things You May Not Know About the Indian Act</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-0.5">Bob Joseph</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Essential context for understanding how the Indian Act shapes daily life — including finances, property, and governance.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">The Wealthy Barber Returns</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-0.5">David Chilton</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Canadian personal finance basics. Conversational, practical, and grounded in how money actually works in this country.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">Tax Is Not a Four-Letter Word</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-0.5">Edited by Alex Himelfarb</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Understanding the Canadian tax system — what it funds, how it works, and why it matters. Useful context for navigating Section 87 and tax filing.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">Wealthing Like Rabbits</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-0.5">Robert R. Brown</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Simple investing explained through storytelling. A friendly entry point for anyone who finds finance intimidating.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">First Nations 101</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-0.5">Lynda Gray</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">A broad overview of First Nations issues in Canada — history, rights, culture, and contemporary realities. Solid foundation for everything else.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Organizations -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-stone-400 tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">Organizations</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-2.5">

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">AFOA Canada</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-0.5">Aboriginal Financial Officers Association</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Financial management training, certification, and resources for Indigenous communities and professionals. afoa.ca</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">Prosper Canada</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Financial empowerment programs including tax filing support, financial literacy training, and benefit access. prospercanada.org</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">Indspire</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Education funding and scholarships for Indigenous students. Administers the Building Brighter Futures bursaries and scholarships program. indspire.ca</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">First Nations Financial Management Board (FNFMB)</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Independent institution supporting First Nations financial governance. Offers certification, capacity development, and financial law review. fnfmb.com</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">NACCA</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-0.5">National Aboriginal Capital Corporations Association</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Network of over 50 Aboriginal Financial Institutions providing business financing, mentorship, and support for Indigenous entrepreneurs. nacca.ca</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">First Nations Information Governance Centre</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Champions the OCAP principles (Ownership, Control, Access, Possession) for First Nations data sovereignty. fnigc.ca</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">Thunderbird Partnership Foundation</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Wellness and mental health support grounded in Indigenous culture. Develops frameworks for community-based wellness. thunderbirdpf.org</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">Native Women's Association of Canada</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Rights and advocacy for Indigenous women. Works on economic empowerment, health, and violence prevention. nwac.ca</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">Assembly of First Nations</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">National advocacy organization representing First Nations citizens in Canada. Policy research, rights advocacy, and intergovernmental relations. afn.ca</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Government Resources -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-stone-400 tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">Government Resources</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-2.5">

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">Indigenous Services Canada</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Federal programs and services including education, health, housing, and infrastructure funding for First Nations, Inuit, and Metis. canada.ca/indigenous-services</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">Non-Insured Health Benefits (NIHB)</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Health benefits for eligible First Nations and Inuit including dental, vision, mental health, medical transportation, and prescription drugs.</p>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-text-primary mt-2">1-800-580-0950</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">Jordan's Principle</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Ensures First Nations children can access the products, services, and supports they need when they need them. Covers health, social, and educational needs.</p>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-text-primary mt-2">1-855-JP-CHILD (1-855-572-4453)</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">CRA Indigenous Peoples</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Tax information specific to Indigenous peoples, including Section 87 guidance, benefit eligibility, and free tax clinics. canada.ca/taxes-indigenous-peoples</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">CMHC On-Reserve Housing</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Housing programs for First Nations communities including new construction, renovation, and homeownership support on reserve. cmhc-schl.gc.ca</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">Nutrition North Canada</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Food subsidy program for isolated northern communities. Subsidizes perishable nutritious food and country/traditional food. nutritionnorthcanada.gc.ca</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Crisis and Support -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-stone-400 tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">Crisis and Support</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-2.5">

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-berry-50 border border-berry-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">Hope for Wellness Help Line</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Immediate mental health counselling and crisis intervention for all Indigenous peoples across Canada. Available in English, French, Cree, Ojibway, and Inuktitut. 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.</p>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-text-primary mt-2">1-855-242-3310</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-berry-50 border border-berry-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">National Indian Residential Schools Crisis Line</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Support for residential school survivors and those affected by intergenerational trauma. Available 24 hours a day.</p>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-text-primary mt-2">1-866-925-4419</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-berry-50 border border-berry-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">Kids Help Phone</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Free, confidential support for young people in Canada. Available by phone, text, or online chat. 24/7.</p>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-text-primary mt-2">1-800-668-6868</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">National Centre for Truth and Reconciliation</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Residential school records, survivor statements, and resources for understanding the history and its ongoing impact. nctr.ca</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Online Tools and Learning -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-stone-400 tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">Online Tools and Learning</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-2.5">

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-r from-clay-50 to-sage-50 border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">Strong Fire</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">You're already here. Free, private, offline-capable financial wellness built for First Nations communities.</p>
          <a href="/" class="text-sm font-medium text-clay-600 mt-2 inline-block hover:underline">Back to home</a>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">FirstVoices</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Indigenous language preservation and revitalization. Online dictionaries, phrasebooks, and language learning tools for over 100 Indigenous languages. firstvoices.com</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">Native Land Digital</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Interactive map of Indigenous territories, treaties, and languages across Turtle Island. An essential tool for understanding whose land you're on. native-land.ca</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">Khan Academy</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Free financial literacy courses covering everything from interest rates to investing to macroeconomics. Self-paced, no account required. khanacademy.org</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-surface-card border border-stone-200 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm leading-snug">Wealthsimple Magazine</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">Accessible Canadian financial content. Articles on saving, investing, taxes, and money psychology written in plain language. wealthsimple.com/magazine</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</Shell>
